272
00:20:50,290 --> 00:20:53,160
- Okay.
- That's really enough.

273
00:20:53,160 --> 00:20:55,090
Are you sure?

274
00:20:55,090 --> 00:20:58,190
Okay. Please wait.

275
00:20:58,190 --> 00:21:02,600
Are you crazy? This is so much! Your whole month's salary is gone.

276
00:21:02,600 --> 00:21:04,610
This...

277
00:21:04,610 --> 00:21:08,290
To be honest, I did Qin Hebo a favor.

278
00:21:08,290 --> 00:21:13,380
He said no matter what I order today, he will be paying for it.

279
00:21:13,380 --> 00:21:16,890
- Really?
- That's why I brought you here.

280
00:21:17,640 --> 00:21:21,630
- Why didn't you say it earlier? You are not lying?
- I'm not.

281
00:21:22,700 --> 00:21:27,000
Excuse me. May I have a menu, please?

282
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:29,390
Since he's paying for it,

283
00:21:29,390 --> 00:21:32,210
I would like some dessert.

284
00:21:32,210 --> 00:21:34,670
I was eyeing them, but I didn't dare order.

285
00:21:34,670 --> 00:21:37,430
I'll have the ice mochi,

286
00:21:37,430 --> 00:21:40,170
and Lingnan egg tarts.
[Lingnan is the area south of the Nanling mountains]

287
00:21:40,170 --> 00:21:42,860
- Two orders of each.
- Do you want to order more?

288
00:21:42,860 --> 00:21:45,410
But you've already ordered a lot.

289
00:21:45,410 --> 00:21:50,220
- Let's also get a pitcher of watermelon juice. I will take them to go if it's too much.
- Okay.

290
00:21:53,160 --> 00:21:56,270
You're not trying to lose weight anymore?

291
00:21:56,270 --> 00:21:58,860
Not today.

292
00:22:10,200 --> 00:22:12,600
I'm so full.

293
00:22:12,600 --> 00:22:14,400
Here is your receipt.

294
00:22:14,400 --> 00:22:17,200
- Vice GM Qin said that you just need to sign it.
- Okay.

295
00:22:18,730 --> 00:22:21,240
So, I can just sign Qin Hebo?

296
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:32,000
Okay, thank you.

297
00:22:34,400 --> 00:22:38,000
Wait! This is the most expensive, I need to finish it.

298
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:40,200
I'm working so hard.

299
00:22:41,900 --> 00:22:44,000
I won't be losing weight today anyway.

300
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:47,000
This is also expensive.

301
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:49,600
These two are the most expensive, and that one is expensive, too.

302
00:22:49,600 --> 00:22:51,200
They are all pretty expensive.

303
00:22:51,200 --> 00:22:53,400
Eat more.

304
00:22:53,400 --> 00:22:55,000
I'll get some for you.

305
00:22:56,000 --> 00:22:57,500
I'm a good eater, right?

306
00:22:57,500 --> 00:22:58,800
Quite good.

307
00:22:59,800 --> 00:23:01,000
You are a very good eater.

308
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:04,900
When I was a kid, I used to eat seven plates at the buffet.

309
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:11,400
Cheers!

310
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:22,600
Hello, this is for you.

311
00:23:22,600 --> 00:23:24,400
Okay, thank you.

312
00:23:29,600 --> 00:23:30,800
You, come over here and help.

313
00:23:30,800 --> 00:23:32,600
Me?

314
00:23:37,200 --> 00:23:39,800
Later there will be a wedding rehearsal, help with playing the music.

315
00:23:39,800 --> 00:23:40,800
I don't know how to play music.

316
00:23:40,800 --> 00:23:43,200
It's really simple, just push a button.

317
00:23:46,200 --> 00:23:48,300
We'll start from this one later on.

318
00:23:55,600 --> 00:23:56,600
- Look, here.
- Okay.

319
00:23:56,600 --> 00:23:58,600
Okay, I understand.

320
00:24:15,800 --> 00:24:16,800
Hello, Shuangshuang.

321
00:24:16,800 --> 00:24:20,200
I have really bad menstrual cramps, can you bring me some medicine?

322
00:24:20,200 --> 00:24:23,000
Okay, I will bring some painkillers.

323
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:24,600
Please hurry.

324
00:24:28,800 --> 00:24:31,800
I forgot the USB!

325
00:24:31,800 --> 00:24:35,400
It's okay. Anan said the hotel has some backup music.

326
00:24:35,400 --> 00:24:39,000
Why am I so forgetful? How could I forget something so important?

327
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:41,600
I've already called them, they should be here soon.

328
00:24:41,600 --> 00:24:43,800
I'll definitely remind you tomorrow.

329
00:24:45,800 --> 00:24:47,400
GM Sheng, I am so sorry for being late.

330
00:24:47,400 --> 00:24:49,510
Hurry up and get started.

331
00:24:51,200 --> 00:24:53,800
Hello, I am Xiao Wang.

332
00:24:53,800 --> 00:24:56,200
Today, Director Guo was busy so I am here in his stead.

333
00:24:56,200 --> 00:25:00,600
I am the wedding company's etiquette trainer and I will also be your emcee.

334
00:25:00,600 --> 00:25:04,800
Today, I will help you guys rehearse.

335
00:25:04,800 --> 00:25:06,000
Let's get started.

336
00:25:06,000 --> 00:25:07,400
- Okay.
- Okay.

337
00:25:07,400 --> 00:25:09,600
One pill should be enough.

338
00:25:14,100 --> 00:25:16,000
Are you okay?

339
00:25:17,400 --> 00:25:21,500
Shuangshuang, why don't you go back and rest? I can help with your work here.

340
00:25:21,500 --> 00:25:24,400
Okay. I need to play the music there.

341
00:25:24,400 --> 00:25:25,400
Okay.

342
00:25:25,400 --> 00:25:26,800
Thank you.

343
00:25:26,800 --> 00:25:29,600
Here, take the water and the medicine.

344
00:25:29,600 --> 00:25:31,000
You're so nice. I'll go lie down.

345
00:25:31,000 --> 00:25:33,200
Hurry, go.

346
00:25:42,100 --> 00:25:44,000
Are you playing the music?

347
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:45,100
It's me.

348
00:25:45,100 --> 00:25:47,300
Later I will use this walkie-talkie to signal you to play the music.

349
00:25:47,300 --> 00:25:50,600
You can just choose any romantic, lyrical song.

350
00:25:50,600 --> 00:25:52,300
Wait a moment.

351
00:25:52,300 --> 00:25:54,800
I want to ask what type of event is being held today?

352
00:25:54,800 --> 00:25:56,800
It's a wedding rehearsal.

353
00:26:10,800 --> 00:26:13,600
If I randomly select one, it should be okay. Right?

354
00:26:15,200 --> 00:26:16,700
This one.
[Violin version, romantic and relaxed, Canon]

355
00:26:18,300 --> 00:26:21,600
GM Sheng and the bride can now enter.

356
00:26:21,600 --> 00:26:24,800
Your steps should be slower.

357
00:26:24,800 --> 00:26:28,600
The bride should look straight ahead and keep smiling.

358
00:26:28,600 --> 00:26:30,000
Nice job.

359
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:31,400
Your steps could be a bit slower.

360
00:26:31,400 --> 00:26:32,800
Your hand

361
00:26:32,800 --> 00:26:35,400
could slightly lift up your wedding gown.

362
00:26:35,400 --> 00:26:37,600
Make sure you don't trip.

363
00:26:37,600 --> 00:26:39,300
Okay, there.

364
00:26:39,300 --> 00:26:43,600
GM Sheng, once you walk the bride there, you can leave the stage.

365
00:26:49,000 --> 00:26:51,000
Projection room, Projection room. Please prepare the music.

366
00:26:51,000 --> 00:26:52,800
Start the music.

367
00:26:53,420 --> 00:26:55,310
Okay, okay.

368
00:26:57,800 --> 00:26:59,000
[Violin version, romantic and relaxed, Canon]

369
00:26:59,000 --> 00:27:03,800
Groom, you can now also walk towards the beautiful bride.

370
00:27:34,500 --> 00:27:36,600
- Mengmeng!
- Mengmeng!

371
00:27:36,600 --> 00:27:39,600
Turn it off! Turn the music off!

372
00:27:39,600 --> 00:27:42,200
Hurry up, turn the music off! Something happened!

373
00:27:45,800 --> 00:27:47,800
Who put on the music?

374
00:27:47,800 --> 00:27:49,600
Who?

375
00:27:51,300 --> 00:27:53,100
It's me.

376
00:27:59,400 --> 00:28:01,900
Let's go, Mengmeng.

377
00:28:03,200 --> 00:28:04,800
Anan.

378
00:28:19,200 --> 00:28:22,700
Brother, I am fine now. Don't worry about me.

379
00:28:27,400 --> 00:28:28,800
It has been so many years,

380
00:28:28,800 --> 00:28:30,400
I did not expect

381
00:28:31,100 --> 00:28:33,600
that you would still be impacted by it.

382
00:28:36,730 --> 00:28:40,220
I have been trying hard to forget about it.

383
00:28:41,710 --> 00:28:43,040
You don't have to.

384
00:28:43,800 --> 00:28:47,800
Brother, that car accident had nothing to do with you.

385
00:28:47,800 --> 00:28:50,200
We should not be living

386
00:28:50,200 --> 00:28:53,300
with these painful memories anymore.

387
00:28:55,800 --> 00:29:00,100
Brother, back then when I first met Zhijuan,

388
00:29:00,100 --> 00:29:02,000
I never thought that

389
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:05,700
he could bring me out of such a state of despair.

390
00:29:05,700 --> 00:29:09,000
I really feel like I am super lucky.

391
00:29:09,000 --> 00:29:13,500
Actually, forgetting about the past pain doesn't mean that

392
00:29:13,500 --> 00:29:17,700
we forget about our longing and feelings for Dad.

393
00:29:19,800 --> 00:29:22,400
Brother, promise me.

394
00:29:22,400 --> 00:29:25,400
We'll try and let go of the past,

395
00:29:25,400 --> 00:29:28,800
and live our present life happily.

396
00:29:28,800 --> 00:29:30,500
Okay?

397
00:29:32,000 --> 00:29:35,200
Okay, I promise you.

398
00:29:35,200 --> 00:29:40,000
Oh right! That music piece today, it was an accident.

399
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:43,700
Sister Xia would not have known about it. Don't blame her.

400
00:29:44,500 --> 00:29:47,000
[Welcome to our wedding reception]
[He Zhijuan & Ning Meng]

401
00:29:47,000 --> 00:29:49,000
Qianqian, I am so sorry.

402
00:29:49,000 --> 00:29:50,700
I really...

403
00:29:50,700 --> 00:29:53,600
If I had known it was their wedding rehearsal,

404
00:29:53,600 --> 00:29:56,400
I would not have let you come even if I was dying.

405
00:29:56,400 --> 00:29:58,300
I am sorry.

406
00:29:59,400 --> 00:30:02,000
I just randomly picked a song.

407
00:30:02,000 --> 00:30:04,400
How did I offend him?

408
00:30:04,400 --> 00:30:07,000
You are talking about Ning Meng?
(T/N: he and she have the same pronunciation in Chinese)

409
00:30:07,000 --> 00:30:10,200
No, it's...

410
00:30:11,700 --> 00:30:13,900
Forget it. There's no point saying it.

411
00:30:13,900 --> 00:30:16,800
Anyway, I, Xia Qian,

412
00:30:16,800 --> 00:30:20,800
don't get along with Evergreen. I don't want to be here again.

413
00:30:20,800 --> 00:30:22,400
I'm leaving now.

414
00:30:24,900 --> 00:30:27,600
Don't get along?

415
00:30:34,400 --> 00:30:36,400
That music piece today.

416
00:30:36,400 --> 00:30:40,700
Sister Xia would not have known about it. Don't blame her.

417
00:30:57,660 --> 00:31:00,850
Xia Qian. Xia Qian.

418
00:31:00,850 --> 00:31:03,200
What's wrong? You have something for me?

419
00:31:05,790 --> 00:31:09,000
Today, my attitude was not good. I'm sorry.

420
00:31:16,300 --> 00:31:22,000
Well... how's Ning Meng? Is she okay?

421
00:31:24,800 --> 00:31:27,800
She wanted me to come here and apologize to you.

422
00:31:27,800 --> 00:31:29,500
Today,

423
00:31:30,500 --> 00:31:33,700
it was me who did not control my emotions.

424
00:31:35,700 --> 00:31:37,800
Then, why

425
00:31:37,800 --> 00:31:40,500
did she have such a big reaction to a music piece?

426
00:31:42,800 --> 00:31:44,900
Because that music piece

427
00:31:44,900 --> 00:31:47,800
is related to my father's car accident.

428
00:31:52,400 --> 00:31:56,400
That year when my father got into the car accident,

429
00:31:56,400 --> 00:32:00,200
that music piece was playing in the car.

430
00:32:00,200 --> 00:32:04,700
After that, Ning Meng was diagnosed with a rare condition.

431
00:32:04,700 --> 00:32:06,900
Every time she hears that music piece,

432
00:32:06,900 --> 00:32:09,300
she remembers that horrible memory.

433
00:32:09,300 --> 00:32:12,800
All these years we have been avoiding that music piece,

434
00:32:12,800 --> 00:32:15,000
we are worried that she would be impacted by it.

435
00:32:15,000 --> 00:32:17,400
I thought that she would have recovered by now.

436
00:32:17,400 --> 00:32:19,600
I didn't expect that today...

437
00:32:22,000 --> 00:32:23,500
I'm sorry.

438
00:32:24,100 --> 00:32:25,800
No,

439
00:32:26,300 --> 00:32:28,840
I'm fine.

440
00:32:28,840 --> 00:32:31,200
I just feel like

441
00:32:31,200 --> 00:32:34,200
at that moment you seemed like a stranger to me.

442
00:32:35,100 --> 00:32:38,200
I understand now, I'm sorry.

443
00:32:41,300 --> 00:32:42,900
How about this?

444
00:32:44,700 --> 00:32:50,000
To make it up, why don't I treat you to a meal?

445
00:32:52,300 --> 00:32:54,100
Okay!

446
00:32:54,100 --> 00:32:57,100
All right. What do you want to eat? I'll make a reservation.

447
00:32:58,300 --> 00:33:00,000
No matter how expensive it is?

448
00:33:00,000 --> 00:33:03,400
Of course. No matter how expensive it is, it's fine.

449
00:33:03,400 --> 00:33:05,900
- Then wait until I rip you off.
- Come on.

450
00:33:05,900 --> 00:33:08,800
- I'll drain all of your money.
- Sure.

451
00:33:17,620 --> 00:33:20,120
You can leave right after you're done.

452
00:33:20,870 --> 00:33:23,770
I did submit my resignation letter, but my last day should be the day after tomorrow.

453
00:33:23,770 --> 00:33:27,170
You're not resigning. You're fired!

454
00:33:27,170 --> 00:33:29,200
Fired?

455
00:33:29,200 --> 00:33:32,110
I haven't received my pay yet. I'm not leaving.

456
00:33:32,110 --> 00:33:35,210
Did you know that today was the wedding rehearsal of GM Sheng's sister?

457
00:33:35,210 --> 00:33:38,180
You screwed up such an important event! How dare you ask for your pay?

458
00:33:38,180 --> 00:33:40,000
You should feel lucky that I'm not asking you to pay for damages!

459
00:33:40,000 --> 00:33:43,110
Playing music was not my job.

460
00:33:43,110 --> 00:33:45,580
You asked me to do it at the last minute.

461
00:33:45,580 --> 00:33:47,690
Why should I take all the blame?

462
00:33:47,690 --> 00:33:50,850
If this is the case, then you should take responsibility for it, too.

463
00:33:50,850 --> 00:33:53,900
So what if I'm responsible?

464
00:33:53,900 --> 00:33:58,350
Even if it's Evergreen's GM standing in front of me, what could he do to me?

465
00:33:58,350 --> 00:34:00,520
- Is that true?
- Vice GM Qin.

466
00:34:00,520 --> 00:34:02,560
Let's leave here, just ignore him.

467
00:34:02,560 --> 00:34:05,050
Vice GM Qin.

468
00:34:05,050 --> 00:34:08,730
I... I didn't mean what I said.

469
00:34:08,730 --> 00:34:11,430
Vice GM... Qin?

470
00:34:11,430 --> 00:34:13,110
Apologize!

471
00:34:14,360 --> 00:34:16,110
I'm sorry.

472
00:34:17,820 --> 00:34:20,410
I just checked all the toilets in the banquet hall.

473
00:34:20,410 --> 00:34:24,080
They are indeed not meeting the sanitary standard the most in our hotel.

474
00:34:24,080 --> 00:34:27,450
I would go and clean them up right away if I were you.

475
00:34:28,210 --> 00:34:30,860
Huh? Y-Yes.

476
00:34:36,160 --> 00:34:37,940
You...

477
00:34:48,480 --> 00:34:49,860
You...

478
00:34:54,800 --> 00:34:57,600
So you're Qin Hebo himself!

479
00:34:57,600 --> 00:34:59,360
You've been lying to me for such a long time!

480
00:34:59,360 --> 00:35:01,140
- I've been lying to you?
- You...

481
00:35:01,140 --> 00:35:05,120
It was you who said that you were well acquainted with Qin Hebo.

482
00:35:05,120 --> 00:35:09,430
I'll tell you the truth. What Qin Hebo owes me...

483
00:35:09,430 --> 00:35:12,060
- is a debt of love.
- A debt of love?

484
00:35:12,060 --> 00:35:16,180
And don't forget, you're the one who said I'm an old driver.

485
00:35:16,180 --> 00:35:18,690
How could you say that I've been lying to you?

486
00:35:18,690 --> 00:35:22,650
The suit and your hair gel. If you aren't a boss, then you are a driver.

487
00:35:22,650 --> 00:35:26,730
A boss wouldn't be on the roof sneaking around feeding a kitten, right?

488
00:35:27,760 --> 00:35:29,380
Yes, that's quite accurate.

489
00:35:29,380 --> 00:35:31,260
My intuition.

490
00:35:33,780 --> 00:35:37,930
Well, if I said anything inappropriate to you during this time,

491
00:35:37,930 --> 00:35:40,520
please don't take it seriously. I'm sorry.

492
00:35:40,520 --> 00:35:43,060
What did you say that was inappropriate?

493
00:35:43,060 --> 00:35:45,900
Not really.

494
00:35:45,900 --> 00:35:49,190
Oh, you said that I owe you a debt of love.

495
00:35:49,190 --> 00:35:51,790
No, no, no. I didn't say that.

496
00:35:51,790 --> 00:35:54,300
I didn't say that!

497
00:35:54,300 --> 00:35:56,100
I'll stop teasing you!

498
00:35:56,990 --> 00:35:59,330
It's getting dark. Shall we go for dinner?

499
00:36:01,520 --> 00:36:04,060
I'm not hungry. I'll skip dinner.

500
00:36:04,060 --> 00:36:06,080
I'm leaving.

501
00:36:06,080 --> 00:36:09,370
Then... will you still come to visit the cat?

502
00:36:10,030 --> 00:36:11,690
See?

503
00:36:14,730 --> 00:36:17,130
She's not moving.

504
00:36:17,130 --> 00:36:18,560
Huh? Well...

505
00:36:33,440 --> 00:36:37,890
It was nice to meet you all these days, little kitty.

506
00:36:37,890 --> 00:36:43,280
But I probably won't be able to visit you very often in the future.

507
00:36:43,280 --> 00:36:45,450
Goodbye.

508
00:36:46,840 --> 00:36:50,500
If you don't come back, what do I do when I often go on business trips?

509
00:36:54,560 --> 00:36:59,030
Then... if he goes on a business trip,

510
00:36:59,030 --> 00:37:01,450
I'll still come back and feed you.

511
00:37:05,530 --> 00:37:07,860
I won't let you starve.

512
00:37:10,760 --> 00:37:14,120
This is so spicy! Why didn't you order anything less spicy?

513
00:37:15,520 --> 00:37:17,970
I've always wanted to ask you a question.

514
00:37:17,970 --> 00:37:19,800
Go ahead.

515
00:37:20,790 --> 00:37:24,390
Why did you decide to become a bargainer in the beginning?

516
00:37:24,390 --> 00:37:27,980
This is an unusual profession.

517
00:37:28,940 --> 00:37:30,950
Of course, it is unusual.

518
00:37:31,540 --> 00:37:33,910
